text:
I ordered the stewed chicken with rice and beans. I didn't get a lot of chicken for the higher price charged. It was $15.00 for the larger container. The same size container everyone else charges $12.00 for. The lady serving the food did not speak English. I asked her how much she charged for it before she started making it. I said 3 times, but she kept making the plate. After she was done, she then went and got a co-worker who spoke English. I was upset, but since she made it already, I took the food. I order the same exact thing at other Spanish food restaurants, and I get 5 pieces of chicken. She only gave me 3 pieces. That's 5 pieces of chicken for $12.00 and 3 for $15.00. Hmm.
I couldn't eat it after a few bites due to the blandness of the food. It needed more seasoning. Even my mother commented on how she needed more salt, which was not on the tables. It was not the food experience I was looking for, and I would not be returning.
The food is very tasty . I had steak and onions with rice and beans, and my friend had pork chops with tostones. The price is very reasonable.

Nice comfy spot to enjoy some classic Dominican eats. Servers are always nice and friendly. Their roasted chicken is nice and juicy. The fries are crisp, and delicious. They have a wide selection of drinks. The mix/pick platter is nice however it’s kind of greasy. Beans and rice is done nicely. The bread pudding is good.

Today is August 11th 2022, and the temperatures have broken so it's only like 85 degrees but it's still warm wife and I walk down from Kew gardens right by last call bar village diner down to mi casa. Is it night before it's very nice friendly sometimes the language differences English and Spanish my Spanish is not that good lead to issues but we've always had great food there had great food there today I had a Cuban my wife had some chicken dish food is great my wife also had Trace leches cake. I posted there latest venues in a few photos again a great place to go one caveat. When we walked in the door was open and the air conditioner was  not on they did turn it on while we were there but it was pretty warm to begin with. That's one of those things when you deal with a small local place and I have a smile on my face cuz they're really good.
Went for lunch with my daughter the food was fresh and tasted great the drinks cold very clean fast service and very polite server's good music to listen to as well

I come to Tropical every Saturday! The music, food and service are all so so wonderful. This food reminds me of home. Now that I live away from my family, Tropical always reminds me that I can find home somewhere else. Jessie and Mafe are both so wonderful to me and my friends. We are always treated so well and with joy. I honestly can’t wait to come back next week!

So disheartening to see so many people leave reviews that aren’t 10/10. This place is INSANE. Food is 10/10. Cocktails??? 10/10. Atmosphere?! 10/10. The food here feels like it came straight from your mother’s kitchen. I come here once a week EVERY week just to eat right and feel like I visited home. Yesi always makes us feel like home, and Mafer hits me with the best drinks. There is literally no where else I go to feel like I’m close to home. Name one Ecuadorian spot that’s better than this. I’ll wait. Name one spot that has a better churrasco or pescado frito. Love you Tropical!!

This place is amazinggg. I go every Saturday. The food, the vibe, and the music is impeccable. Highly recommend the fried fish and mojito (my fav). The fact that this place isn't 5 stars breaks my heart. As a South American it's been so hard to find a place that feels like home. Jessie and MaFer are literal angels and great us with the best energy every time!

I ordered from this place regularly until I realized they were changing the prices on their menu items. 1/2 pollo asado is $9.99 (cash; $10.39 by card) according to their menu, and it comes with your choice of side. I've ordered from them multiple times and am used to paying this. The last time they charged me $18 for the same platter, and when I asked why that is... they gave me a poor excuse, saying that the menu prices do not include the side (despite it showing clearly that it does). I'm not a fan of this kind of business, it's predatory. And that's a shame because their food is actually good.

The food is good. The service is mediocre and your charged 20% regardless the number of people in your party. The food items are charged separately. In addition, there is a surcharge if you charge with your credit card. I suggest you go
elsewhere. The food is just not worth the price point of charges.

Solid diner. A little far from the subway unless you're a local or have a car. The entrance to the parking lot is a little funky unless you enter from 2 directions (north and west).

I took a gamble and tried their brisket sandwich. It was about the same price as the burger I was going to order so why not? When it arrived I was skeptical. It was kinda grey and uniform in color. Visually it didn't look as appealing as a smoked brisket with darker singed edges from a BBQ joint. But more often then not smoked briskets come out dry and overcooked. One bite of this and I am hooked. This was perfectly moist and tender and a little fatty the way meat should be. The meat could be pulled apart but not rubbery.

My friend said the western omelets and the Irish breakfast. They cleaned their plates. Would recommend 100%

If you're looking for a true classic diner experience with a modern twist, Bel Aire Diner in Queens is the spot! From the moment we walked in, we were hit with the warm, welcoming vibe that makes you feel right at home. The retro booths, bright signage, and cozy aesthetic give that perfect throwback feel like stepping into a movie scene.

The food? Absolutely fantastic. We tried a little bit of everything: disco fries, mozzarella sticks, chicken tenders with their signature sauce, and the Chupacabra Burger, which was a flavor bomb in the best way possible. Their Candy Shop Belgian Waffle was the sweetest ending to our meal, and the Broadway Smoothie was a hit for my little one!

But what really made this visit special was the staff. Our server, Adrian, deserves a huge shout-out! He was attentive, friendly, and made sure we had everything we needed. It's rare to find service that feels this personal and genuine.

Bonus points: Kids eat FREE! A huge perk for families!

Whether you're stopping by for a quick bite or a full meal, Bel Aire Diner is an absolute must in Queens. Amazing food, top-notch service, and a vibe that keeps you coming back. Can't wait to visit again!

Love love love !! I haven’t been in a diner in 17 years and I couldn’t have been happier with this experience all over again. The atmosphere was great with the seating booths and the staff was professional and very friendly. Of course I order my very favourite silver dollar pancakes that were very delicious. I’m so happy we had a chance to visit this restaurant on our trip.

I love a classic NYC diner with retro vibes and Bel Aire certainly has that. It’s a bit of a hike from the subway but worth it for a great weekend brunch. The menu is huge and there’s something on it for everyone but I tend to stick mostly to breakfast classics at diners like this and their corned beef hash served with three eggs and topped with melted cheese hit the spot. Great service, great food and great atmosphere - I’ll be back

I’ve been going to the diner since I was a kid and the food and service has always been outstanding. I used them for catering for my birthday party last night and the food was spectacular and they were on time. I had people telling me all night how great the food was. Will definitely use them for my events in the future and 💯 endorse their catering services as well. Bel Aire team - thank you for helping make my event a success!
Burn pizza hard and won't be eating there again. $14 for 3 plain & 2liter coke

We wanted an authentic pepperoni pie, and looked at a few different places before deciding on Lulu's. There were two people working, a young man and an older gentleman. Both greeted me enthusiastically. It took almost no time to get the pizza boxed up and ready to go, and they were very attentive to my needs, chatting in a friendly fashion and giving me a kit with plates and spices since I was getting it to go. The pizza was delicious! Crispy crust, excellent sauce, cooked to perfection. Lulu's was fantastic, highly recommend.
Slices are always tasty, saucy if you order during the day. Had one late evening, a pizza slice so thin, ok, but not great. You're still hungry after one slice. Two expensive.

Small Place Big on Food And Service
They are known for repeat customers
Serving really delicious pizza and great customer service is what Lulu’s Pizza is all about. You even get a free can of soda or a free bottle of water when you order two slices of the plain pizza for a total of $5, a sweet deal that can’t be beat!!!
The place is super clean, the service is very efficient, the pizza comes out the oven crispy and super hot EVERY time!!! Even the tables outside are clean.
Although outside seating is limited, the tables for the most part are usually available as this is a busy shopping area (directly opposite Queens Center Mall) and people eat their pizza quickly and are on their way. I VERY HIGHLY recommend this place because the owner and the staff go out of their way to make the experience worthwhile (great food and great service). Although this is a relatively small place, you will keep coming back for more.
The guy Adan, who makes the pizza and then gives it to you with smile, is super friendly and I have ALWAYS seen him constantly working so hard and yet he goes out of his way to be nice.
Additionally they also have desserts, like Tiramisu, Cannoli, cheesecake and the likes, plus heroes, pattie’s, rolls, Italian Ices, French Fries, chicken fingers and mozzarella sticks.
And yes, they also serve coffee.
The best pizza in the neighborhood and just found out it’s Halal! My family and friends will be so happy! Great pizza men and Lou, “old school” Italian, has fantastic customer service!

I believe that their service is very quick. You get a pretty big slice of cheese pizza for 3 dollars however I have had pizza this big and this reasonable in terms of price but tasted better than this spot. Though I must say if you’re looking for a quick bitter for your child if they’re hungry you can stop there and buy a slice or two.
I ordered for the first time via UberEats ..I enjoyed a 20" pizza pie with thin crust the way I like it. It was tasty and huge slices. Great price, too!

Very disappointed I came here. I came here simply on a whim because I saw a sign outside that advertised Philly cheesesteaks. The first thing I did was ask the owner how much for a Philly cheesesteak and he told me $7. I sat down and the waitress wanted me to have something to drink when I never asked for it and did not give me the option of having water. She never even served me water. Although they made my Philly cheesesteak the way I wanted it , with very little onions, the meat was less than stellar.it was chewy. After I finished my meal, the waitress told me that my bill came out to $11. When I ask them how come they told me $7 when I first came in, one of the people that was cooking told me the prices had changed. When I looked on the price list inside the store it’s at $8.99 for a Philly cheesesteak sandwich. Even with taxes, it would not be $11 in the state of New York. He told me that the prices have changed, but he still had the old price up. I feel this is deceptive advertising and I recommend that you stay clear of this place. It’s obvious that the reviews that are positive about this place were generated either by employees or family members.Even the stock images that they have bear no reflection whatsoever on all the food that is being served. If that wasn’t bad enough the place was not clean I even photographed napkins on the floor and no one even bother to clean them up. Because of their actions, it leaves me no choice but to contact the Better Business Bureau, as well as the Board of Health.
The pizza was delicious and we loved the chicken quesadilla!
Family owned and the best place to get food on Jamaica Ave. Food tastes great, prices are fair and service is friendly. Been coming here for eight years and never once had a bad experience.

Service attentive, clean and quiet (Tuesday lunchtime). Food not so great. It’s old school. Like when restaurants did not make much from scratch and bought premade coleslaw, frozen fries and burger patties and factory meat (pic included of ‘chicken gyro’). Eggs and french toast were better as those were made from scratch. Fine if that’s your speed but not for me.

Breakfast with an old friend on a Sunday morning, 8AM. Friendly service and the coffee cup kept full. Only two other diners when we arrived which made seating quick and food arrived long after order was placed. Prices are reasonable. Atmosphere is old school as this diner has been around forever, clean. Food was your basic diner fare. Had a French Toast Deluxe, no complaints here. I've had better but the food was good here, won't wow you but won't be disappointed either. Glad to see this diner is still here as lots of small businesses appear to be gone on Austin Street.

Even after looking through the reviews, I wanted to give this place a chance. It’s located on Austin street and I’ve had good success with most restaurants in the area

The quality of the food is most important and they have seem to forget about it. Food was terrible.

Very disappointing.

I've read a lot of bad reviews for this place but that was after I stopped in for dinner. The interior of this place is definitely dated and in need of a renovation. Old diners like this are either cool and retro or not so cool and kind of dirty. This one had a dirty vibe. (The bathroom is gross) The salt and pepper shaker on my table looked like it hadn't been cleaned since the 70s.  My server was fine, but she was not the friendliest person. She spoke very little ... just took my order and disappeared for a good half hour. Ironically she was the one that told me the place closes at 7:30 when I walked in at 6:30. I thought — who cares, I have plenty of time. Little did I know my order wasn't going to come out for 30 minutes! It felt like I was sitting there forever. I finished my water and then asked for a drink when she finally came back 30 minutes later. The diner was NOT busy. Maybe 3 other tables had guests. I ordered comfort food — chopped steak with mashed potatoes and corn. It was a large portion and it was good. The mashed potatoes and gravy had an odd color but everything was tasty. It was the vibe of the place that put me off. A man came in at one point with the food that he had picked up earlier, screaming about how it was undercooked. The owner took the food out of the container and handed it back to the cook. I'm not even sure what it was. It was just so off putting, especially NOW after reading so many reviews about that kind of thing. I worried later, about whether I would have a stomach ache "later" and I did not. So overall, my food was very good, the service and atmosphere was odd. I wouldn't go back as I would try somewhere else on Austin Street ... and there were tons of places!

Stop by after an appointment across the street. The diner was very busy on a Saturday morning. Waitress was sweet and accommodating. Decor is very rustic old school diner. Food took a little while to come out but was very good and tasty.

I just don't understand why they charge 3 percent to use a credit card when paying for your meal. There should be no extra charge.

Really really delicious food! I loved the pesto cream cheese bagel, my husband loved the lox bagel, and my six-year-old ate the entire tropical waffle! The owner is really nice too, as is the rest of the staff!

The presentation and taste of this breakfast plate are absolutely delightful. The vibrant freshness of the ingredients reflects the care and thought put into its preparation. The perfectly cooked sunny-side-up eggs are complemented by a colorful salad bursting with flavors—crisp greens, juicy cherry tomatoes, creamy feta cheese, and briny olives. The addition of sliced avocado and deliciously seasoned pastrami adds a luxurious touch, while the toasted whole-grain bread provides a wholesome balance. The small bowl of rich butter and fruity jam in the center is a charming and classic detail that ties everything together beautifully.

I recently visited Chakra Cafe, and it was an incredible experience! The ambiance is warm and inviting, with a calming vibe that makes you feel right at home. The staff is friendly and attentive, always ensuring you have everything you need. The menu offers a variety of delicious options, from fresh coffee to mouth-watering desserts. I especially loved their signature lattes and ocean bagel. Everything was beautifully presented and tasted amazing. I highly recommend this spot for anyone looking to relax and enjoy great food. Definitely a 5-star experience!

One of the best fruits and nutella waffles I've ever tried (Chakra Waffle). They have a menu with a lot of variety so every time I pass by and I am hungry I get to try different things. Really good food quality
Great options ranging from sandwiches, bagels, salads, and smoothies! I got the smoked salmon salad and there was a good amount of salmon in the bowl. They also offer gluten free (Udi) bread.

Been coming here for yearsssss! This is an absolute gem in Woodside. I love their lattes and pastries. Huge shoutout to the staff who are always so friendly and welcoming. Highly recommend their new seasonal drink, Mad Purple made with purple sweet potato cream latte made with their homemade purée.

Update:
Fast forward 2025: the Fruit Croffle was a nice surprise. See photo 📸

Old Review:
Cheese Danish and Croissant. Good bread!
Hot and Cold brew Coffees. Great aroma!
Thank you for your courtesy.

My wife and I decided to try this place for breakfast and we were blown away. The food was amazing. I got the grilled cheese bacon sandwich and it was the best sandwich I have ever had. It was perfect. My wife had the fruit croissant waffle and it was so delicious. We both got mixed berry smoothies and were very impressed. This place is amazing and we are so glad we got the experience it.
Good coffee in a nice setting with very friendly staff. Try the macaroons. They're really good.

Lovely place; the lady who prepared our drinks LITERALLY did it with love. She is very generous with any extra cream, chocolate or cinnamon for your drink. The place is aesthetically clean and organized so you are sure to enjoy your drink without stress.
